#: ../../_doc/user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-devices.md:104
#: a9a5fadeb28d4420a25e2b6ac0144e84
msgid ""
"Actions are applicable to every DEVICE_CLASS and expose some additional "
"options."
msgstr ""

#: ../../_doc/user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-devices.md:106
#: 62c8ebf51ffa4f70b452508b920658c5
msgid "Listing Devices"
msgstr ""

#: ../../_doc/user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-devices.md:108
#: ddf93bf1d50347b58816e97e096833f0
msgid ""
"The `list` action lists known devices in the system. `list` accepts VM-names"
" to narrow down listed devices. Devices available in, as well as attached to"
" the named VMs will be listed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../_doc/user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-devices.md:112
#: e960a04bf1b945f4897e9f550f7f9976
msgid "`list` accepts two options:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../_doc/user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-devices.md:114
#: 667fcfd352964393af25dd87887b06cb
msgid ""
"`--all` - equivalent to specifying every VM name after `list`. No VM-name "
"implies `--all`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../_doc/user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-devices.md:116
#: d506d091c3564b46ab0f1d1239d89555
msgid "`--exclude` - exclude VMs from `--all`. Requires `--all`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../_doc/user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-devices.md:119
#: 57b5ad357b884106ba589dad29eed115
msgid ""
"**SYNOPSIS** `qvm-device DEVICE_CLASS {list|ls|l} [--all [--exclude VM [VM "
"[...]]] | VM [VM [...]]]`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../_doc/user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-devices.md:122
#: 80b56e47154a4f57babbc85999cbbe28
msgid "Attaching Devices"
msgstr ""

#: ../../_doc/user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-devices.md:124
#: 0e88cfabc52645788c331276f0b7ccfc
msgid ""
"The `attach` action assigns an exposed device to a VM. This makes the device"
" available in the VM it's attached to. Required argument are targetVM and "
"sourceVM:deviceID. (sourceVM:deviceID can be determined from `list` output)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../_doc/user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-devices.md:129
#: 01f786eed53841a99084b3eb8d7acaa3
msgid "`attach` accepts two options:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../_doc/user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-devices.md:131
#: 1324e154f5fa4a6c9bab5fdefdf41817
msgid ""
"`--persistent` - attach device on targetVM-boot. If the device is "
"unavailable (physically missing or sourceVM not started), booting the "
"targetVM fails."
msgstr ""

#: ../../_doc/user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-devices.md:133
#: 23b3d20b3ea34a2eb1ff8a924aa04fda
msgid "`--option`, `-o` - set additional options specific to DEVICE_CLASS."
msgstr ""

#: ../../_doc/user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-devices.md:135
#: d29028ed42da4a2cb70b97df3b0c0178
msgid ""
"**SYNOPSIS** `qvm-device DEVICE_CLASS {attach|at|a} targetVM "
"sourceVM:deviceID [options]`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../_doc/user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-devices.md:138
#: f5593a83173d4b19b88e408dbecdd92e
msgid "Detaching Devices"
msgstr ""

#: ../../_doc/user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-devices.md:140
#: b6d43051e6ae4d319be31ed6c740b043
msgid ""
"The `detach` action removes an assigned device from a targetVM. It won't be "
"available afterwards anymore. Though it tries to do so gracefully, beware "
"that data-connections might be broken unexpectedly, so close any transaction"
" before detaching a device!"
msgstr ""

#: ../../_doc/user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-devices.md:144
#: 17ca501ba01841c091cbaff32b4bb81b
msgid ""
"If no specific `sourceVM:deviceID` combination is given, *all devices of "
"that DEVICE_CLASS will be detached.*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../_doc/user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-devices.md:146
#: 74bcce11e8984beebac67c965aebdbec
msgid "`detach` accepts no options."
msgstr ""

#: ../../_doc/user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-devices.md:148
#: 745239eb1fe14a1fb25a09dc981f5b7e
msgid ""
"**SYNOPSIS** `qvm-device DEVICE_CLASS {detach|dt|d} targetVM "
"[sourceVM:deviceID]`"
msgstr ""
